2d:T57c,West Texas Intermediate (WTI) Crude Oil remains the primary pricing benchmark for North American crude production and a globally referenced marker for light sweet crude grades. XRT Group sources WTI directly from Midland Basin and Permian production regions, bypassing traditional broker intermediaries through our pre-vetted supplier network.

**Grade & Quality**

XRT-sourced WTI typically presents at 39.5–40.5° API gravity with sulfur content below 0.25% — meeting refinery specifications for both FCC and hydrocracking configurations. Each parcel undergoes mandatory SGS or Bureau Veritas inspection at load port, with quantity and quality certificates issued under ASTM D287 and D4052 methodology.

**Pricing & Benchmarks**

Pricing is negotiated against the prevailing NYMEX WTI front-month contract. XRT's current indicative premium is +$0.85/BBL over benchmark, subject to volume, INCOTERMS, and delivery window. Forward price locks are available through our Structured Trade Finance desk under UCP 600 LC structures.

**Logistics & Delivery**

Primary loading terminals: Corpus Christi, Beaumont, Nederland (TX). FOB or CIF delivery available. Transit times: 12–18 days to ARA, 28–35 days to Singapore.

**Compliance**

All cargoes subject to OFAC screening, IMO 2020 sulfur compliance documentation, and FATF AML counterparty due diligence. Vessel vetting per CDI and OCIMF standards.28:["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-12 pt-10 sm:pt-16 pb-10 sm:pb-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_400px] gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-start","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps px-3 py-1.5 border","style":{"color":"#c8111f","borderColor":"#c8111f"},"children":"ENE-001"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps text-[#A8A5A0]","children":"Energy Commodities"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[clamp(2.25rem,6vw,4.5rem)] text-white leading-[1.0] mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","fontWeight":900,"letterSpacing":"-0.02em","textTransform":"uppercase"},"children":"WTI Crude Oil"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base text-[#A8A5A0] mb-8","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)","letterSpacing":"0.04em"},"children":"40° API / 0.24% Sulfur"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base sm:text-lg text-[#C4C1BE] leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-xl","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)"},"children":"WTI Crude Oil sourced directly from Midland Basin and Permian production. 40° API, 0.24% sulfur. NYMEX WTI benchmark at +$0.85/BBL. Minimum 100,000 BBL, FOB or CIF. SGS and Bureau Veritas inspection. <4 hour desk response."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 border-t border-xrt-steel/15","children":[["$","div","Min. Volume",{"className":"py-5 sm:py-6 border-b sm:border-b-0 sm:border-r border-xrt-steel/15 sm:px-6 sm:first:pl-0","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"label-caps text-[#A8A5A0] mb-2","children":"Min. Volume"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-black text-white","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","letterSpacing":"-0.02em"},"childre